# SEO Implementation Rules

This project uses the `artesaos/seotools` package to manage meta tags and SEO. Follow these rules when implementing or updating SEO-related logic.

## 1. Global Configuration
- Core settings are located in `config/seotools.php`.
- Default values (Title, Description, Site Name) should be updated there if they apply to the entire site.

## 2. Layout Integration
- Always include `{!! SEO::generate() !!}` within the `<head>` of your main layout file (`resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php`).
- Remove any manual `<title>` or `<meta name="description">` tags to avoid duplicates.

## 3. Controller Usage (Preferred)
Set SEO values inside Controller methods using the `SEOTools` facade. This keeps SEO logic out of the views.

```php
use Artesaos\SEOTools\Facades\SEOTools;

public function show(Product $product)
{
    SEOTools::setTitle($product->name);
    SEOTools::setDescription($product->summary);
    SEOTools::setCanonical(url()->current());
    SEOTools::opengraph()->setUrl(url()->current());
    SEOTools::opengraph()->addProperty('type', 'articles');
    SEOTools::twitter()->setSite('@yourhandle');

    return view('product.show', compact('product'));
}
```

## 4. Best Practices
- **Titles**: Use `SEOTools::setTitle()` to set the page-specific title. The package handles separators and site names based on `config/seotools.php`.
- **Descriptions**: Keep descriptions between 150-160 characters for optimal search engine display.
- **OpenGraph**: Always set the `url` and `type` for Social Media sharing.
- **Images**: Use `SEOTools::opengraph()->addImage($imageUrl)` for dynamic content like blog posts or products.
- **Avoid Blade Sections**: Do not use `@section('title')` or `@section('description')` in Blade views; migrate that logic to the Controller.
